### 1. Launch and Initial Focus

When your application starts, Orca should announce the window title and initial focused element:

```csharp
public class MainWindow : Window
{
    public MainWindow()
    {
        Title = "My Accessible Application";

        // Set initial focus to meaningful element
        var firstButton = new Button 
        { 
            Text = "Get Started",
            AutomationId = "GetStartedButton"
        };

        Content = new VerticalStackLayout
        {
            Children = { firstButton }
        };

        // Ensure focus is set after window loads
        Loaded += (s, e) => firstButton.Focus();
    }
}
